Required:

* JDK installed
* An Android SDK (> Android 9)
* npm installed
* npx installed (npm packet)

You need to set env paths:
* ANDROID_SDK_ROOT = C:\Users\$USER\AppData\Local\Android\Sdk
* NVM_HOME = C:\Users\$USER\AppData\Roaming\nvm
* NVM_SYMLINK = C:\Program Files\nodejs
* PATH = %NVM_HOME%;%NVM_SYMLINK%;C:\Users\$USER\AppData\Local\Android\Sdk\platform-tools

Then execute this command inside the ReactNativeApp folder and install everything it tells you to

* npx react-native run-android
